CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1784722711
OL,3,CInflation falls to 2.6% as food and
OL,4,Cfuel prices drop in 15-month low
OL,6,FThe lower-than-expected CPI rate is
OL,7,Fset to provide some relief to the new
OL,8,Fprime minister, who has made efforts
OL,9,Fto ease the cost of living a top
OL,10,Fpriority.
OL,12,FAccording to the ONS, the biggest
OL,13,Fdownward pull on overall inflation
OL,14,Flast month came from transport, food
OL,15,Fand non-alcoholic drinks.
OL,17,FAverage petrol prices declined by 2.1p
OL,18,Fper litre between May and June, while
OL,19,Fdiesel prices dropped by 10.7p per
OL,20,Flitre.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1784722711
OL,3,CInflation falls to 2.6% as food and
OL,4,Cfuel prices drop in 15-month low
OL,6,FThis marked the first time petrol had
OL,7,Feased since the start of the Middle
OL,8,FEast conflict at the end of February,
OL,9,Fwhich sent oil and gas prices soaring
OL,10,Fand pushed up prices at the pumps.
OL,12,FHowever, while prices were lower month-
OL,13,Fon-month, overall motor fuel prices
OL,14,Fremained 21.3% higher in the year to
OL,15,FJune in a sign that the conflict has
OL,16,Fdriven up the cost of living in the UK.
OL,18,FFood and non-alcoholic drink prices
OL,19,Ffell by 0.2% between May and June,
OL,20,Fbringing the annual inflation rate
OL,21,Fdown to 1.7%, from 2.2% in May.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/7
